headline: EQT (EQT) Is Up 7.0% After Strong Q3 Growth and New Asian Export Plans Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: EQT Corporation recently reported better-than-expected third quarter results, with sales volumes rising 9.1% year-over-year and average sales prices up nearly 40%, leading to significantly higher revenues and earnings that exceeded analyst consensus. A unique insight from recent developments is EQT’s ongoing focus on expanding natural gas production in the Appalachian Basin, coupled with ambitious plans to begin exporting to Asian markets from 2030 to address growing global LNG demand.
